What a sick sick world we live in. Most people are careless and heartless with no clue on what love means. Addictions take over people and they hurt the people they love, so blinded by their addiction that the day they step back to reality, they have lost everything. Everybody blames everyday. People that have so much given to them for FREE do not appreciate it. The more good you do for someone, the more trust you have for them, the more people take advantage of it and I give up on giving one shit about people. 22 years of living and seeing the world as a fucked up world that is getting worse day by day. Growing up I thought that when Im 21 Ill go clubbing, have the time of my life, this that but its the complete opposite. All I have on my mind is money and it is my fault for helping out people that needed it but have no intention to return it, leaving me with all the debt for helping them out. Ive never been so done with everyones bullshit to force myself to be heartless too. People want nothing but misery for one another and I feel really really bad for people that throw away their life with excuses when opportunities to benefit themselves. People say that I just talk to the wrong people but until proven, I will always believe that the world is a cruel, cold, and heartless place that I need to distant myself from. People think they know you. They think they know how youre handling a situation. But the truth is, no one knows. No one knows what happens after you leave them, when youre lying in bed or sitting over your breakfast alone. They dont know whats going on inside your head--the mind-numbing cocktail of anger and sadness and guilt. This isnt their fault. They just dont know. And so they pretend and they say youre doing great when youre really not. And this makes everyone feel better. Everybody but you.
